version_description: Version 1 is lacking chords. This version is much easier to read and use and is generally more user-friendly
It has more details in the chords
This tab is more detailed in that it has more chord changes than other tabs I have seen. It also seems more accurate to me.
Optimization of version 1 where to play the chords and added 2/3 chords where I thought it sounds more like the original.
I felt other version are overly complicated, and convoluted. With G/F# or G/B when F is easier and less intimidating for a beginner. plus chordify suggested Dm in place of the E.
